27/02/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The interior ministers of the five Western Balkan states -- Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Croatia, Macedonia and Serbia-Montenegro -- signed a joint declaration Friday (25 February) regarding intensified co-operation on border management. The officials met in Skopje at a conference titled "Border Security Systems" that was organised by the Geneva-based Centre for Democratic Control of Armed Forces. (MIA, A1 TV - 25/02/05)
